igher Education Educational Psychology Kinesiology, Health Promotion, and Recreation Teacher Education and Administration Kristin Farmer Autism Center People Faculty and Staff Directory Deans and Administration New Faculty and Staff Endowed Chairs and Professorships Emeritus Faculty Awards, Promotions, and Tenure Dean's List Students Alumni and Friends Newsletter Where Are They Now? Campaign Development Board Giving to the COE The Department of Teacher Education and Administration focuses on the preparation of highly competent educators, researchers, and administrators. The University of North Texas has prepared educators since its founding in 1890. Courses provide philosophical, psychological, and sociological backgrounds to support educational decision-making. Educational Leadership faculty develop leaders for schools and school districts who promote social equity, excellence, and engaged learning and teaching. Department of Teacher Education and Administration Preparing Tomorrow's Educators and Scholars "Each year our district will recruit and select approximately 200 teachers. The first place we look is the University of North Texas... The graduates from UNT are the epitome of professional educators." Dr. Jamie WilsonSuperintendent, Denton Independent School District The Department of Teacher Education and Administration integrates theory, research and practice to generate knowledge and to develop educational leaders who advance the potential of all learners. Undergraduate Programs Degrees with Teacher Certification Graduate Programs Non-Degree and Certification Programs Honors and Accomplishments Faculty and Staff Contact Us Scholarships Resources Read TEA Time, our departmental newsletter! COE’s Castro elected to NAEYC Governing Board UNT names Elizabeth Murakami Mike Moses Endowed Chair Teacher Education and Administration earns inaugural equity and diversity award More Announcements » Department of Teacher Education and Administration Contact Information Col